Commentary Text: Mishra to Manish Pandey, out Caught by Rabada!! Weird shot from Pandey!! He had just come in and this isn't the easiest of surfaces to start on. Looks to take Mishra on with the slog sweep but is done in flight and gets a top-edge that's pouched comfortably at deep mid-wicket. It's that longer part of the ground which undid MI yesterday in Dubai, and just like that here in Abu Dhabi, has taken out Pandey today. He was clutching his hamstring last over, so did that play a role in this shot? Either ways, DC aren't complaining. This is a fab phase for them. Manish Pandey c Rabada b Mishra 3(5)

Commentary Text: Mishra to Warner, out Caught by Pant!! Another attempted reverse sweep and Pant reckons there was some glove on that. The Capitals have reviewed the caught behind call. This looks close, think Warner might be in trouble, looked like a feather on the glove. UltraEdge in and there's a minor spike when the ball is past Warner's gloves. That's enough for the third umpire to overturn the original call. Warner is OUT. Think it's a fair decision from the third umpire, Chris Gaffaney. The spike wasn't huge, but there seemed to be a deviation when the ball went past the gloves - Warner was attempting the reverse sweep to one that drifted across him - caught the glove and Pant stood low to hold on. A wicket against the run of play, the dangerous Warner departs. Warner c Pant b Mishra 45(33) [4s-3 6s-2]
